From: Brian <brian@luna.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Add penultimate layer hidden state extraction API

Add llama_get_embeddings_penultimate_ith() — retrieves the hidden state
from the second-to-last transformer block (before final RMSNorm),
equivalent to HuggingFace's hidden_states[-2].

Motivation: Diffusion model text encoders (Lumina-2, Flux-style
architectures) are trained against pre-norm penultimate layer outputs,
not the post-norm final embeddings that llama_get_embeddings_ith()
returns. Without this API, anyone using llama.cpp as a text encoder
for image generation gets the wrong representation.

The implementation follows the same pattern as the existing embeddings
API: buffer allocation, GPU->CPU async copy, output reordering, and a
per-token getter function. Model builders opt-in by storing the residual
stream into res->t_embd_penultimate before the final norm — currently
implemented for Qwen3 and Qwen3-VL, trivially extensible to other
architectures.

Changes:
  include/llama.h          - API declaration
  src/llama-graph.h        - t_embd_penultimate tensor + getter
  src/llama-graph.cpp      - reset() + set_outputs()
  src/llama-context.h      - buffer_view + method declaration
  src/llama-context.cpp    - buffer alloc, GPU copy, getter, reorder, C API
  src/models/qwen3.cpp     - capture point before final norm
  src/models/qwen3vl.cpp   - capture point before final norm

---
diff --git a/include/llama.h b/include/llama.h
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/include/llama.h
+++ b/include/llama.h
@@ -990,6 +990,13 @@ extern "C" {
     // returns NULL for invalid ids.
     LLAMA_API float * llama_get_embeddings_ith(struct llama_context * ctx, int32_t i);
 
+    // Get the penultimate layer (pre-norm) embeddings for the ith token.
+    // Returns the hidden state BEFORE the final RMSNorm/LayerNorm, matching
+    // HuggingFace hidden_states[-2]. Required for diffusion model conditioning
+    // where the text encoder was trained against pre-norm representations.
+    // shape: [n_embd] (1-dimensional)
+    // Returns NULL if the model does not provide penultimate embeddings or embeddings are not enabled.
+    LLAMA_API float * llama_get_embeddings_penultimate_ith(struct llama_context * ctx, int32_t i);
 
